blocks.content: If ` F ` is a function and ` A ` and ` B ` both follow ` X ` in the transitive closure of ` F ` , then (for distinct ` A ` and ` B ` ) either ` A ` follows ` B ` or ` B ` follows ` A ` in the transitive closure of ` F ` (or both if it loops). Similar to Proposition 133 of [Frege1879] p. 86. Compare with ~ frege133 . (Contributed by RP, 18-Jul-2020.)
